ClaimX is a multi-role expense reimbursement platform built using Java 17 and Spring Boot. It supports four roles — Employee, Manager, Finance, and Admin — each with their own workflows for raising, approving, processing, and auditing claims. I independently designed and developed the entire backend, which included a MySQL database with 5 tables and 24 REST APIs covering the full claim lifecycle. Authentication was handled using JWT tokens, authorization was managed through Spring AOP, and all APIs were documented with Swagger and tested via Postman.
